&gt;Hugo&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a class="link" href="https://stack.jimmycai.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt; theme and automatically deploy it to GitHub Pages via GitHub Actions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before you begin, necessary preparations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; account [for hosting site files and displaying blogs]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://git-scm.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;git&lt;/a&gt; [Push site files to GitHub]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Linux basics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id="reference-links"&gt;Reference Links
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a class="link" href="https://brume.top/p/build-your-personal-blog-with-hugo" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://brume.top/p/build-your-personal-blog-with-hugo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class="link" href="https://letere-gzj.github.io/hugo-stack/p/hugo/custom-blog" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://letere-gzj.github.io/hugo-stack/p/hugo/custom-blog&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
&lt;a class="link" href="https://github.com/CaiJimmy/hugo-theme-stack-starter" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
&gt;https://github.com/CaiJimmy/hugo-theme-stack-starter&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="environmental-description"&gt;Environmental Description
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 24.04.3 LTS&lt;br&gt;
git version 2.43.0&lt;br&gt;
hugo v0.151.1-1cdd17882c28a9f23278d38ef03b403954cfb1e5+extended&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="local-website-building"&gt;Local website building
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Execute the following command in the terminal, replacing &lt;code&gt;site-name&lt;/code&gt; with your desired name.&lt;br&gt;
hugo new site &lt;code&gt;site-name&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hugo does not provide themes by default, so you need to import themes yourself. Here we use the Stack theme created by Jimmy Cai.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;div class="chroma"&gt;
&lt;table class="lntable"&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt; 9
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;10
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="lnt"&gt;11
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class="lntd"&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Add the Stack theme and use its default configuration and examples &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Replace site-name, GitHub-username, local-IP&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;cd&lt;/span&gt; site-name
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;git init
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;git submodule add https://github.com/CaiJimmy/hugo-theme-stack/ themes/hugo-theme-stack
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;cp -r themes/hugo-theme-stack/exampleSite/content/* content/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;cp themes/hugo-theme-stack/exampleSite/hugo.yaml ./
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;rm -f hugo.toml
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;rm -rf content/post/rich-content
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;sed -i &lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;s|example.com|GitHub-username.github.io|&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; hugo.yaml
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;hugo server -D --baseURL&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;http://local-IP:1313 --bind&lt;span class="o"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;local-IP
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now, visit http://&lt;code&gt;local-IP&lt;/code&gt;:1313 to preview your blog.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="github-auto-deploy"&gt;GitHub Auto Deploy
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create two GitHub repositories​​:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A repository named &lt;code&gt;site-name&lt;/code&gt;, Used to store site source files.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A ​​public​​ repository named &lt;code&gt;GitHub-username&lt;/code&gt;.github.io, Used to host static pages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol start="2"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate a GitHub token​​:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Go to home ​​Settings → Developer Settings → Personal access tokens​​ -&amp;gt; Token(classic)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a token(classic) and save it to Settings -&amp;gt; Secrets and variables -&amp;gt; Actions in the site name repository.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ol start="3"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create .github/workflows/deploy.yaml:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
